## 7. Bento Grid Block

**Type**: `bento-grid` · **Purpose**: Asymmetric layout — 2 small items stacked on the left, 1 large item on the right.

![Bento Grid](C:/Users/User/.gemini/antigravity/brain/95306e18-9900-4d81-8437-b355e45affa2/13_bentogrid_v2_1771541015499.png)

### Data Structure

```json
{
  "type": "bento-grid",
  "items": [
    { "media": "/images/small1.jpg", "mediaType": "image", "span": "small", "caption": { "en": "Detail 1", "ge": "დეტალი 1" } },
    { "media": "/images/small2.jpg", "mediaType": "image", "span": "small", "caption": { "en": "Detail 2", "ge": "დეტალი 2" } },
    { "media": "/images/feature.jpg", "mediaType": "image", "span": "large", "caption": { "en": "Main Feature", "ge": "მთავარი" } }
  ]
}
```

| Field | Required | Options | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `items[].media` | ✅ | path | Media path |
| `items[].mediaType` | ✅ | `"image"` / `"video"` | Type |
| `items[].span` | ✅ | `"small"` or `"large"` | `small` = stacks on left, `large` = fills right column |
| `items[].caption` | Optional | text | Caption overlay |

